What you need to know:

While most Kenyans are aware of the Galana-Kulalu Irrigation Scheme, which collapsed after gobbling up more than Sh10 billion, there are many more little schemes that died that no one wants to talk about.Acting Tana Delta Irrigation Project (TDIP) manager, Mr Andrew Moroni, said that they have started doing some engineering works to repair infrastructure damaged when the project stalled.